wns: [[Cowra, New South Wales|Cowra]], [[Mudgee]], [[Parkes, New South Wales|Parkes]] and [[Lithgow, New South Wales|Lithgow]]; smaller centres, such as [[Oberon, New South Wales|Oberon]] and [[Forbes, New South Wales|Forbes]]; and small towns and villages such as [[Canowindra, New South Wales|Canowindra]], [[Cudal, New South Wales|Cudal]], [[Molong, New South Wales|Molong]], [[Grenfell, New South Wales|Grenfell]], [[West Wyalong, New South Wales|West Wyalong]], [[Portland, New South Wales|Portland]], [[Wallerawang]], [[Condobolin, New South Wales|Condobolin]] and [[Eugowra, New South Wales|Eugowra]].\n\n===Demography and area===\nThe following [[Local government areas of New South Wales|local government areas]] are contained within the region:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:right\"\n|+Population by Local Government Area\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Central West rank\n! scope=\"col\" | Local Government Area\n! scope=\"col\" | Population 30 June  2016<ref name=\"3218.0\">{{cite web |publisher=Australian Bureau of Statistics |title=3218.0 \u2013 Regional Population Growth, Australia, 2016 |url=http://www.abs.gov.au/AUSSTATS/abs@.nsf/allprimarymainfeatures/797F86DBD192B8F8CA2568A9001393CD?opendocument |access-date=9 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305015843/http://www.abs.gov.au/AUSSTATS/abs@.nsf/allprimarymainfeatures/797F86DBD192B8F8CA2568A9001393CD?opendocument# |archive-date=5 March 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" | 10 year growth rate\n! scope=\"col\" | Population density (people/km<sup>2</sup>)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 1\n| [[Bathurst Regional Council]]\n| 42,389\n| 14.8\n| 11.1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2\n| [[City of Orange (New South Wales)|Orange City]]\n| 41,384\n| 13.8\n| 145.6\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 3\n| [[Mid-Western Regional Council]]\n| 24,569\n| 13.5\n| 2.8\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 4\n| [[City of Lithgow|City of Lithgow Council]]\n| 21,524\n| 6.6\n| 4.8\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"